def: To feign with an evil design. [Obs.] Spenser.

An opening affording entrance or exit; orifice; aperture; as:(a) The opening of a vessel by which it is filled or emptied, chargedor discharged; as, the mouth of a jar or pitcher; the mouth of thelacteal vessels, etc.(b) The opening or entrance of any cavity, as a cave, pit, well, orden.(c) The opening of a piece of ordnance, through which it isdischarged.(d) The opening through which the waters of a river or any stream aredischarged.(e) The entrance into a harbor.
That part of a bridle or halter which encompasses the head.Shak.
The tribal history of forms; that part of phylogeny whichtreats of the tribal history of forms, in distinction from the tribalhistory of functions. Haeckel.
A performer upon the viola di gamba. See under Viola.
A covering or incrusting with marble; a casing of marble; avariegating so as to resemble marble. [R.]
Full of clots, or clods. "Clotty matter." Harvey.
The native black race of Papua or New Guinea, and the adjacentislands.
Of or pertaining to yesterday; relating to the day last past.
